Frontier Airlines plans to charge up to $100 of passengers who want to stow hand luggage on their flight.
Frontier Airlines intends to charge up to $100 for a piece of hand luggage and $2 for coffee or lemonade, although the announcement on Wednesday read that passengers may keep the entire can.
The new fee applies to hand luggage in the luggage compartment above the seat, small pockets under the seat are still free of charge.
