Fees are a way to get passengers to take less on board.
O'Malley said the new fee isn't really about making money.
It’s about Frontier’s most loyal customers, who would have clearly expressed that it’s becoming increasingly difficult to find room in the compartment above the seat.
Passengers who buy tickets on the airline’s website do not have to pay.
This means that a passenger may be able to take one piece of baggage free of charge at the gate of Frontier, but the next person will have to pay $100 for a similar piece of baggage.
