The relationship in question is not simply that of a drug dealer, but of a drug dealer who supplies his lawyer with drugs.
Some of his communications were unquestionably legitimate, for he was the advocate of these persons.
But that went far beyond the boundaries of a normal relationship between lawyer and client.
He countered the police investigation as much as possible so that they could continue to pursue their criminal activities.
Mr. Ditta thus brought his profession into disrepute.
